  "texts": [
    "While characterizing all of these homologs is beyond the scope of this work, as a proof of concept, we performed a deeper analysis of two of these candidate IDRs.",
    "We first examined the N-terminal IDR of the DYRK-family kinase Yak1 and its homologs.",
    "Despite large variation in sequence length (248-420 residues), the Yak1 homologs displayed notably conserved dimensions, with all but two sequences having a predicted R e between 109 and 122 Å (Fig. 6c).",
    "In contrast, basic polymer models predict R e differences of >27 Å across this range of sequence lengths, suggesting that there may be evolutionary constraints on the R e of the N-terminal Yak1 IDR.",
    "Analysis of the IDR sequences reveals several trends in sequence features that may explain the buffering of chain dimensions."
